      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="P00731D2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Steel</hi> was buried in the Church-Yard of <hi rend="underline">Lithmahegow</hi>, by some of his Friends; who, after the <hi rend="underline">Revolution</hi>, erected a fair <hi rend="underline">Monument</hi>, on <hi rend="underline">Pillars</hi>, over his <hi rend="underline">Grave</hi>, and caused an <hi rend="underline">Epitaph</hi> to be engraved on the <hi rend="underline">Stone</hi>, in Words to this Effect.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Here lyeth the Body of </hi>Captain David Steel, <hi rend="underline">a Saint, who was murdered by </hi>John Creichton<hi rend="underline"> (with the Date underneath</hi>.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1">Some of my <hi rend="underline">Friends Burlesqued</hi> this <hi rend="underline">Epitaph</hi>, in the following Manner.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="4" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-4"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-4-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-4-line-group-1-line-1">Duke <hi rend="underline">Hamilton</hi>, in <hi rend="underline">Queen Ann</hi>'s Time, informed me of this Honour done to that infamous <hi rend="underline">Rebel</hi>, and when I had said to his <hi rend="underline">Grace</hi>, that I wished he had ordered his <hi rend="underline">Foot-Men</hi> to <hi rend="underline">demolish</hi> the <hi rend="underline">Monument</hi>; the Duke answered, he would not have done so for <hi rend="underline">Five Hundred Pounds</hi>, because it would be an Honour to me as long as it lasted.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="5" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-5"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-5-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-headnote-5-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-line-1"> Here lies the Body of Saint <hi rend="underline">Steel</hi>,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-P00731D2-line-2"> Murdered by <hi rend="underline">John Creichton</hi>, that <hi rend="underline">Dee'l</hi>.P00731D2   </l></lg></div>
